1. Accuracy: It is the ratio of the number of correct responses to the total number of questions asked.
2. Precision: It is the ratio of the number of correct responses to the total number of responses given by the chatbot.
3. Recall: It is the ratio of the number of correct responses to the total number of correct responses that the chatbot could have given.
4. F1-score: It is the harmonic mean of precision and recall.

## 5. Conclusion

In this paper, we presented a novel dataset, Wiki7Wonders, for the 7WoD task. The dataset consists of 1,470 question-answer pairs extracted from the Wikipedia pages of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. We evaluated the performance of several pre-trained models on the dataset and showed that the models perform poorly on this task. We also presented a simple baseline model that performs significantly better than the pre-trained models. The results indicate that the 7WoD task is challenging and requires further research.

We believe that the Wiki7Wonders dataset can be used to train and evaluate models for the 7WoD task, as well as for other similar tasks that require the identification of a list of items from a given text. The dataset can also be used to develop models that can generate a list of items given a natural language description.
